    <item>
      <title>How to link old and new IDs when migrating data from one table to another</title>
      <link>https://l-lin.github.io/post/2018/2018-03-29-postgresql_insert_and_link_ids/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 29 Mar 2018 11:25:34 +0200</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://l-lin.github.io/post/2018/2018-03-29-postgresql_insert_and_link_ids/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;When proceeding a database migration, I often had to create a temporary table that will contains
the data from the old database.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;However, after the migration, I still need to have links between the old IDs and the new IDs for
various post migration operation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is about creating the table containing the linked ids.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    
